Package app

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Controller
    Uses View, Estimation, DelayProfile, DataAccess and DataRead.
    DataAccess
    Uses a hash table (generated using DataRead) to store the flights.
    DataRead
    Reads the flight information from the file and puts it into a hash table.
    DelayProfile
    A representation of the profile which we will show to the user.
    Estimation
    The Estimation class calculates the expected delays of the flight.
    FlightEvent
    An abstract data type to represent a flight event.
    Key
    Class Key is used as a method to use both airline name, and airport as a key in the hash table Used in DataAccess, DataRead,
    Landing
    An abstract data type to represent a landing event.
    PathFinding
    Finds the shortest and the second shortest path between two airports, so that the user has a choice about which path is better.
    TakeOff
    An abstract data type to represent a take off.
    View
    Shows the user the screen where the user can make choices and shows the output.
